  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API. Rate limiter middleware is part of the standard pipeline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization runs BEFORE the rate limiter (auth must succeed for the policy to read `userOid`/`tenantId`). Authentication failure short-circuits with 401; the rate limiter never sees the unauthenticated request.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Policy registration via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension (or equivalent registration site). Module total ≤15 non-framework registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Rate limiter is on the endpoint surface — no new CRUD→AI dependencies. Policy reads context from `HttpContext.User`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">**PRIMARY**. Rate limiting on Action `/run` endpoints. Per-user soft cap on Tool dispatches/hour. Per-tenant soft cap on AI Tool invocations/day. MVP soft enforcement only (warnings + telemetry); hard caps deferred to R2. Return clear 429 ProblemDetails.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Typed options class for thresholds. Startup validation. Documented default values + environment behavior.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">429 response uses ProblemDetails (RFC 7807) with `status: 429`, `title: "Too Many Requests"`, `detail: "..."`, `Retry-After` header.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages — `Microsoft.AspNetCore.RateLimiting` is in framework.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement = BFF, publish-size unchanged (no new packages), no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Soft MVP semantics: limit exceeded → 429 + telemetry; next bucket window opens normally. NO hard block beyond the response. NO admin override surface in MVP.</constraint>
  </constraints>

