  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Confirm task 040 (ActionEndpoints.cs) shows ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md AND the `EnableRateLimiting("ai-action-invocation")` slot exists on every endpoint. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Load `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` and answer the pre-merge checklist in `notes/decisions/task-044-bff-extensions-checklist.md`. Confirm no new NuGet packages — `Microsoft.AspNetCore.RateLimiting` is in framework. Cite placement = BFF (spec.md §6).</step>
    <step order="2">Create `Configuration/RateLimitingOptions.cs` per ADR-018 typed-options conventions. Fields: `PerUserHourlyCap` (int, default 60), `PerTenantDailyCap` (int, default 1000), `Enabled` (bool, default true), `BucketIsolationByTenant` (bool, default true — tenant id is part of partition key). Add validation attributes.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Infrastructure/RateLimiting/AiActionInvocationPolicy.cs`. Implement using `PartitionedRateLimiter.Create&lt;HttpContext, string&gt;`. Partition function: `ctx =&gt; $"user:{ctx.User.FindFirst("oid")?.Value}|tenant:{ctx.User.FindFirst("tid")?.Value}"`. Per-partition: stacked `FixedWindowRateLimiter` — one for user (1 hour window, cap = `PerUserHourlyCap`), one for tenant-wide aggregation (1 day window, cap = `PerTenantDailyCap`). The tenant-wide limiter partitions by `tenant:{tid}` only.</step>
    <step order="4">Configure the rejection callback (`options.OnRejected = (ctx, ct) =&gt; { ... }`) to emit App Insights custom event `action_engine.ratelimit.exceeded` with properties `userOid`, `tenantId`, `endpointPath`, `bucketWindow`. Return a ProblemDetails JSON body with status 429, title "Too Many Requests", detail describing which bucket exceeded, and a `Retry-After` header with the seconds until the next bucket window opens.</step>
    <step order="5">CRUD endpoints (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE) policy decision: either (a) same `ai-action-invocation` policy (simplest), or (b) separate `ai-action-crud` policy with a more permissive cap. Recommend (a) for MVP — CRUD volume is typically much lower than `/run` volume. Document the decision in `notes/decisions/rate-limiting-thresholds.md`.</step>
    <step order="6">Register the rate limiter middleware in `Program.cs`: `builder.Services.AddRateLimiter(options =&gt; { options.AddPolicy("ai-action-invocation", new AiActionInvocationPolicy(opts)); options.RejectionStatusCode = 429; });`. Place `app.UseRateLimiter()` AFTER `UseAuthentication()` + `UseAuthorization()` in the pipeline. Register `RateLimitingOptions` via `services.Configure&lt;RateLimitingOptions&gt;(config.GetSection("RateLimiting"))`.</step>
    <step order="7">Edit `appsettings.json` to add a `RateLimiting` section with the default values + a comment block explaining the soft-MVP semantics. Edit `appsettings.Development.json` to override with permissive values for local dev (e.g., 1000/hour, 10000/day).</step>
    <step order="8">Write integration tests at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/ActionEngine/RateLimitingIntegrationTests.cs`:
      (a) 60 requests from same user succeed; request 61 within the hour returns 429 with ProblemDetails body + `Retry-After` header;
      (b) After 1-hour window passes (test-clock advance), request 1 in the new bucket succeeds — no permanent block;
      (c) Per-tenant cap kicks in: multiple users from same tenant collectively hitting 1000 requests/day all get 429 even if no individual user hit their cap;
      (d) App Insights event fires on every 429 (use a test-double sink and assert the event was recorded).</step>
    <step order="9">Write `notes/decisions/rate-limiting-thresholds.md` documenting: default thresholds + rationale, how to tune via `appsettings.json` per environment, soft-MVP semantics (no hard block), what changes in R2 (hard caps + admin override + per-Tool cost-class differentiation).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the new options + policy + Program.cs edit + appsettings edits; `adr-check` verifies ADR-016 (rate limiting present, soft MVP), ADR-018 (typed options + startup validation), ADR-019 (429 returns ProblemDetails + Retry-After), ADR-029 (no new packages). Re-run `dotnet build` and integration tests.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 044 ✅. Verify it unblocks tasks 060, 061, 062, 063 (the integration test phase). Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-044-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

